Biography

Career

Games/Starts: 90/89

Colgate Debut: Nov. 10, 2021, at Cornell

Career Stats: 1048 points (11.6 ppg), 323 rebounds (3.6 rpg), 192 assists (2.1 apg), 39.0 FG% (395-1013), 26.5 3FG% (67-253), 79.9 FT% (191-239), 2704 minutes (30.0 mpg)

Awards

2023-2024 All-Patriot League Second Team

2023-2024 Preseason All-Patriot League Team

2022-2023 All-Patriot League Second Team

2023-2024 (Junior)

Games/Starts: 33/32

All-Patriot League Second Team

Scored team-high 402 points, averaging 12.2 ppg

Became 23rd player in Colgate women's basketball history to eclipse the 1,000 point mark

Currently sits at 20th all-time in points in program history

21 games in double figures and led the team in scoring 14/34 games

Posted double-double against UMBC (11/11/23) with 15 points and a career-high 11 boards

2022-2023 (Sophomore)

Games/Starts: 30/30

Led the team in points and rebounds at 12.5 per game and 4.1 per game, respectively.

Shot 40.1% from the field, logging season totals of 53 steals, 16 blocks, 65 assists, and 120 rebounds

Career-high 24 points to propel the team to an opening day victory against Cornell.

Career-high nine rebounds in a road victory against Holy Cross and three blocks against Army West Point.

2021-2022 (First Year)

Games/Starts: 29/29

Earning a starting spot in every game her first year season, finished the year at just over 10 points per game and shooting 38.3% from the field.

Grabbed 85 boards, dished out 69 assists, and added 41 steals

Season high 21 points against Loyola Maryland, seven rebounds against ACC opponent Syracuse, and seven assists at Navy.

Before Colgate

Edwin O. Smith High School in Storrs, Connecticut … Senior-year captain and junior-year tri-captain...As senior, averaged 12.0 points, 4.6 rebounds, 2.6 assists, 2.9 steals and 0.5 blocks … For career, averaged 17.1 points, 5.1 rebounds, 2.8 assists, 4.3 steals and 0.7 blocks...Nominated as 2020-21 Connecticut Girls Basketball Gatorade Player of the Year … Two-time CHSCA Class LL All-State … Three-time All-Central Connecticut Conference … Helped Panthers to 2020 and 2021 Central Connecticut Conference titles...Played for Connecticut Attack in AAU basketball ... Ran multiple skill development clinics and sessions for that club and served as assistant coach for sixth-grade Attack team in 2020-21.

Personal

Born: Taylor Anne Golembiewski in Hartford, Connecticut.

Family: Parents are Brian and Leigh Golembiewski … Has one sister.
